You see what Shakespeare's doing here?
He's using words to create emotions.

07:04.958 --> 07:06.083
What kind of words are these?

07:06.708 --> 07:09.083
They're violent words.
And why is this important?

07:09.583 --> 07:12.000
Because when you feel angry, when you
wanna punch somebody in the face

07:12.375 --> 07:13.917
you put it on paper instead.

07:14.042 --> 07:18.167
You find words that evoke emotions in you
and you do something positive with it.

07:18.625 --> 07:19.500
Edwin.

07:21.625 --> 07:24.667
I could have sworn I saw the principal
take the phone from you this morning.

07:25.000 --> 07:26.167
Guess what?

07:26.500 --> 07:30.417
If you applied yourself half as much to
class as you do to scamming the school

07:30.833 --> 07:32.417
you could accomplish anything.

08:05.000 --> 08:06.125
Ready to suffer?

08:06.792 --> 08:07.917
Bring it on.

08:31.750 --> 08:33.917
- Thank you.
- I'll see you. / I'll see you.

08:35.750 --> 08:36.417
I'm this way.

08:36.832 --> 08:38.292
- Goodnight.
- Bye. / Bye.

09:18.583 --> 09:20.458
Bitch, huh?

09:22.375 --> 09:23.375
Get in!

09:34.625 --> 09:35.625
Really.

09:36.083 --> 09:38.667
Check mate and mate, mate.

09:40.167 --> 09:41.625
